# Phase 1: Candidate Interface & LLM Proxy

## 🎯 What Are We Building?

Phase 1 is the **foundation** of the GUIDE platform. By the end of this phase, a candidate can:

1. **See a task description** (Library Management System requirements) in a left sidebar
2. **Write code** in a professional Monaco code editor (same editor used in VS Code!)
3. **Chat with an AI** (Google Gemini) through a chat panel on the right

Think of it as building a **coding workspace with a built-in AI assistant**.

---

## 📚 Concepts You'll Learn

| Concept | Where Used |
|---|---|
| **Monaco Editor** | The code editor component from VS Code, embedded in React |
| **Three-panel layout** | CSS Grid/Flexbox for sidebar + editor + chat |
| **REST API proxy** | Backend forwards your messages to Google Gemini |
| **LLM API integration** | Calling Google Gemini API from Python |
| **Event logging** | Saving every prompt/response to MongoDB (seed of interaction trace Φ) |

